<subSubSection id="B2A7F089A544FFA0CF9BFD3EA0F0FE59" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA02A302A544FFA0CF9BFD3EA620FB39" blockId="28.[144,782,327,2079]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
be applied to the BR or to the FR morphotype? As detailed by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC7BFD72A6A0FD19" author="REGTEREN ALTENA C. O. VAN" box="[266,643,743,767]" journalOrPublisher="Basteria" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 6" part="27" publicationUrl="http://natuurtijdschriften.nl/download?type=document&amp;docid=596445" refId="ref28546" refString="REGTEREN ALTENA C. O. VAN 1963. Notes sur les limaces. 8. Sur l'etat de deux especes nominales du genre Arion. Basteria 27: 1 - 6. http: // natuurtijdschriften. nl / download? type = document &amp; docid = 596445" title="Notes sur les limaces. 8. Sur l'etat de deux especes nominales du genre Arion" type="journal article" year="1963">VAN REGTEREN ALTENA (1963)</bibRefCitation>
, LINNAEUS’ (1758) description of 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CCD5FC9EA5F8FCF9" box="[420,475,775,799]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">rufus</emphasis>
referred to his book on the Swedish fauna (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CCF9FCB1A618FCD9" author="LINNAEUS" box="[392,571,807,831]" journalOrPublisher="Wishoff, Lugduni Batavorum" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26796" refString="LINNAEUS [LINNAEUS] C. 1746. Fauna Svecica sistens animalia Sveciae Regni: qvadrupedia, aves, amphibia, pisces, insecta, vermes, distributa per classes &amp; ordines, genera &amp; species. Cum differentiis specierum, synonymis autorum, nominibus incolarum, locis habitationum, descriptionibus insectorum. Wishoff, Lugduni Batavorum. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 34892" title="Fauna Svecica sistens animalia Sveciae Regni: qvadrupedia, aves, amphibia, pisces, insecta, vermes, distributa per classes &amp; ordines, genera &amp; species. Cum differentiis specierum, synonymis autorum, nominibus incolarum, locis habitationum, descriptionibus insectorum" type="book" year="1746">LINNAEUS 1746</bibRefCitation>
; but the implied Swedish occurrence must almost certainly have been 
<taxonomicName id="3DBDD881A544FFA0CDABFCF1A63CFC99" authority=": ODHNER 1951" authorityName="ODHNER" authorityYear="1951" box="[218,543,871,895]" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Arion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CDABFCF1A542FC99" box="[218,353,871,895]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Arion fuscus</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC03FCFEA63CFC99" author="ODHNER N. H." box="[370,543,871,895]" editor="BRINK P. &amp; WINGSTRAND K. G." journalOrPublisher="C. W. K. Gleerup, Lund" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="26 - 50" refId="ref27381" refString="ODHNER N. H. 1951. Swedish high mountain Mollusca. In: BRINK P., WINGSTRAND K. G. (eds). The mountain fauna of the Virihaure area in Swedish Lapland. C. W. K. Gleerup, Lund, pp. 26 - 50." title="Swedish high mountain Mollusca" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="The mountain fauna of the Virihaure area in Swedish Lapland" year="1951">ODHNER 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CF41FCF2A4ECFC79" author="PROSCHWITZ T. VON" journalOrPublisher="Fauna och Flora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="121 - 138" part="80" refId="ref27804" refString="PROSCHWITZ T. VON 1985. Roda skogssnigeln Arion rufus (L.), en mellaneuropeisk art stadd i snabb spridning med manniskan i Sverige. Fauna och Flora 80: 121 - 138." title="Roda skogssnigeln Arion rufus (L.)" type="journal article" volumeTitle="mellaneuropeisk art stadd i snabb spridning med manniskan i Sverige" year="1985">VON PROSCHWITZ 1985</bibRefCitation>
), to German material described by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CF1AFC1EA4C5FC59" author="ALDROVANDI U." journalOrPublisher="Cum indice copiosissimo. Ferronium, Bonon" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref23999" refString="ALDROVANDI U. 1644. De animalibvs insectis libri septem cvm singvlorvm iconibvs ad viuum expressis. Cum indice copiosissimo. Ferronium, Bonon." title="De animalibvs insectis libri septem cvm singvlorvm iconibvs ad viuum expressis" type="book" year="1644">ALDROVANDI (1644)</bibRefCitation>
, and to the work of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC9CFC31A6BBFC59" author="LISTER M." box="[493,664,935,959]" journalOrPublisher="Smith, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref27018" refString="LISTER M. 1685. Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior. Smith, Londini." title="Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior" type="book" year="1685">LISTER (1685)</bibRefCitation>
, who described both British and French specimens. Because both BR and FR forms occur on the Continent, but FR or 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CD93FB9EA4D7FBF9" box="[226,244,1031,1055]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">fr</emphasis>
are almost unknown in Britain (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CF08FB9EA4ECFBD9" author="CHEVALLIER H." journalOrPublisher="Universite de Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref24757" refString="CHEVALLIER H. 1974. Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique. Ph. D. Thesis, Universite de Paris." title="Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique" type="book" year="1974">
CHEVALLIER 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CDE5FBBEA4ECFBD9" box="[148,207,1063,1087]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">1974</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CD97FBB1A5DBFBD9" author="ROWSON B. &amp; ANDERSON R. &amp; TURNER J. A. &amp; SYMONDSON W. O. C." box="[230,504,1063,1087]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="91907" part="9" refId="ref28738" refString="ROWSON B., ANDERSON R., TURNER J. A., SYMONDSON W. O. C. 2014 a. The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20 %. PLoS ONE 9 (3): e 91907. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0091907" title="The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20" type="journal article" year="2014">ROWSON et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
), greater certainty is achieved by selecting a British specimen as the lectotype. Also this choice follows Recommendation 74A of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC4AFB1EA5E0FB79" author="ICZN" box="[315,451,1159,1183]" journalOrPublisher="International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26201" refString="ICZN 1999. International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London." title="International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition" type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
) in ensuring compatibility with the nomenclature of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CCA7FB3EA691FB59" author="CHEVALLIER H." box="[470,690,1191,1215]" journalOrPublisher="Haliotis" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="7 - 23" part="2" refId="ref24732" refString="CHEVALLIER H. 1972. Arionidae (Mollusca, Pulmonata) des Alpes et du Jura francais. Haliotis 2: 7 - 23." title="Arionidae (Mollusca, Pulmonata) des Alpes et du Jura francais" type="journal article" year="1972">CHEVALLIER (1972</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CFB2FB3EA6DDFB59" author="CHEVALLIER H." box="[707,766,1191,1215]" journalOrPublisher="Universite de Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref24757" refString="CHEVALLIER H. 1974. Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique. Ph. D. Thesis, Universite de Paris." title="Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique" type="book" year="1974">1974</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CDBAFB51A5F1FB39" author="ROWSON B. &amp; ANDERSON R. &amp; TURNER J. A. &amp; SYMONDSON W. O. C." box="[203,466,1223,1247]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="91907" part="9" refId="ref28738" refString="ROWSON B., ANDERSON R., TURNER J. A., SYMONDSON W. O. C. 2014 a. The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20 %. PLoS ONE 9 (3): e 91907. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0091907" title="The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20" type="journal article" year="2014">ROWSON et al. (2014a</bibRefCitation>
, b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA02A302A544FFA0CDCCFB7EA0F0FE59" blockId="28.[144,782,327,2079]" lastBlockId="28.[809,1443,263,1791]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Hereby we designate as the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="3DBDD881A544FFA0CFB5FB71A5B2FAF9" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Limax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CFB5FB71A4ECFAF9" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Limax rufus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CDADFA9EA5B2FAF9" author="LINNAEUS" box="[220,401,1287,1311]" journalOrPublisher="Salvius, Holmiae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26868" refString="LINNAEUS [LINNAEUS] C. 1758. Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata. Salvius, Holmiae. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" title="Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
a now non-existing specimen amongst those described by 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC86FAB1A6E0FAD9" author="LISTER M." box="[503,707,1319,1343]" journalOrPublisher="Smith, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref27018" refString="LISTER M. 1685. Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior. Smith, Londini." title="Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior" type="book" year="1685">LISTER (1685: 7)</bibRefCitation>
from “Amberry” in Yorkshire. Amberry is Almondbury, south of Huddersfield, which may still be pronounced as Lister wrote it and appears with spellings similar to Lister’s in contemporary documents (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CDD1FA5EA515FA39" author="SMITH A. H." box="[160,310,1479,1503]" journalOrPublisher="English Place-Name Society, Vol. XXXI. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref29441" refString="SMITH A. H. 1961. The place-names of the West Riding of Yorkshire. Part II. Osgoldcross and Agbrigg Wapentakes. English Place-Name Society, Vol. XXXI. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge." title="The place-names of the West Riding of Yorkshire. Part II. Osgoldcross and Agbrigg Wapentakes" type="book" year="1961">SMITH 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC3EFA51A5D4FA39" author="TAYLOR J. E." box="[335,503,1479,1503]" journalOrPublisher="Kirklees Libraries and Museum Service" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="7 - 10" refId="ref29511" refString="TAYLOR J. E. 1975. &quot; Ambry &quot;. In: Historic Almondbury: the village on the hill. Kirklees Libraries and Museum Service, pp. 7 - 10." title="Ambry" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Historic Almondbury: the village on the hill" year="1975">TAYLOR 1975</bibRefCitation>
). The illustration of “ 
<taxonomicName id="3DBDD881A544FFA0CDEBFA7EA512FA19" box="[154,305,1511,1535]" class="Gastropoda" family="Limacidae" genus="Limax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Limax rufus</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC23FA71A5C4FA19" author="LISTER M." box="[338,487,1511,1535]" journalOrPublisher="Smith, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref27018" refString="LISTER M. 1685. Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior. Smith, Londini." title="Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior" type="book" year="1685">LISTER 1685</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1 on tabula 2), to which 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CD98F991A590F9F9" author="LINNAEUS" box="[233,435,1543,1567]" journalOrPublisher="Salvius, Holmiae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26868" refString="LINNAEUS [LINNAEUS] C. 1758. Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata. Salvius, Holmiae. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" title="Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata" type="book" year="1758">LINNAEUS (1758)</bibRefCitation>
also refers (he originally indicated “ p. 1” but in the 12th edition—LINNÉ 1767: 1081—corrected this to “t. 2. f. 1”), is plausibly of an individual from this population, since foreign localities, but not British ones, are consistently included in the captions to others of LISTER’ s (1685) figures, and Amberry is the single British locality for the species mentioned in the main text. In any case, since the illustration does not reveal anatomical characters, it is better to associate the lectotype with the named locality, from which fresh specimens can be collected, than to designate an illustrated specimen of uncertain origin. (Recommendation 74E of the Code (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CC57F83EA597F859" author="ICZN" box="[294,436,1959,1983]" journalOrPublisher="International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26201" refString="ICZN 1999. International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London." title="International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition" type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
) trumps Recommendation 74B, which applies only “other things being equal”.) It is unlikely that any of LISTER’ s (1685) specimens of this species survive. In 1683 he deposited a collection of specimens illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0C9A2FE91A158FEF9" author="LISTER M." box="[1235,1403,263,287]" journalOrPublisher="Memoriae &amp; Rationi. Martyn, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26954" refString="LISTER M. 1678. Historiae animalium Angliae tres tractatus. Unus de araneis. Alter de cochleis tum terrestribus tum fluviatilibus. Tertius de cochleis marinis. Quibus adjectus est quartus de lapidis ejusdem insulae ad cochlearum quandam imaginem figuratis. Memoriae &amp; Rationi. Martyn, Londini. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 65746" title="Historiae animalium Angliae tres tractatus. Unus de araneis. Alter de cochleis tum terrestribus tum fluviatilibus. Tertius de cochleis marinis. Quibus adjectus est quartus de lapidis ejusdem insulae ad cochlearum quandam imaginem figuratis" type="book" year="1678">LISTER (1678)</bibRefCitation>
in the Ashmolean Museum, and an accompanying letter promised more; so perhaps the specimens described in 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CE3DFEF1A7D7FE99" author="LISTER M." box="[844,1012,359,383]" journalOrPublisher="Smith, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref27018" refString="LISTER M. 1685. Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior. Smith, Londini." title="Appendicis ad historiae animalium Angliae, tres tractatus, &amp; c. Altera editiio, auctior &amp; emendatior" type="book" year="1685">LISTER (1685)</bibRefCitation>
, the appendix to 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0C9B5FEF1A14FFE99" author="LISTER M." box="[1220,1388,359,383]" journalOrPublisher="Memoriae &amp; Rationi. Martyn, Londini" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26954" refString="LISTER M. 1678. Historiae animalium Angliae tres tractatus. Unus de araneis. Alter de cochleis tum terrestribus tum fluviatilibus. Tertius de cochleis marinis. Quibus adjectus est quartus de lapidis ejusdem insulae ad cochlearum quandam imaginem figuratis. Memoriae &amp; Rationi. Martyn, Londini. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 65746" title="Historiae animalium Angliae tres tractatus. Unus de araneis. Alter de cochleis tum terrestribus tum fluviatilibus. Tertius de cochleis marinis. Quibus adjectus est quartus de lapidis ejusdem insulae ad cochlearum quandam imaginem figuratis" type="book" year="1678">LISTER (1678)</bibRefCitation>
, followed them. Nothing of this collection is known to have survived (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CE93FE31A0E3FE59" author="MACGREGOR A." box="[994,1216,423,447]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the History of Collections" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="125 - 144" part="13" refId="ref27046" refString="MACGREGOR A. 2001. The Ashmolean as a museum of natural history, 1683 - 1860. Journal of the History of Collections 13: 125 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jhc / 13.2.125" title="The Ashmolean as a museum of natural history, 1683 - 1860." type="journal article" year="2001">MACGREGOR 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2A7F089A544FFA0CE20FE51A753FC19" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA02A302A544FFA0CE20FE51A753FC19" blockId="28.[809,1443,263,1791]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
We associate our BR morphotype with 
<taxonomicName id="3DBDD881A544FFA0C865FE51A1B9FE39" box="[1300,1434,455,479]" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Arion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ater" subSpecies="rufus">
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C865FE51A1B9FE39" box="[1300,1434,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. ater rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because in Britain the 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C935FE7EA078FE19" box="[1092,1115,487,511]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">br</emphasis>
haplogroup is widespread (combining information from COI and 16S sequences) whereas the 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CE82FDBEA026FDD9" box="[1011,1029,551,575]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">fr</emphasis>
haplogroup is known from only a single locality (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CE97FDD1A0C4FDB9" author="ROWSON B. &amp; ANDERSON R. &amp; TURNER J. A. &amp; SYMONDSON W. O. C." box="[998,1255,583,607]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="91907" part="9" refId="ref28738" refString="ROWSON B., ANDERSON R., TURNER J. A., SYMONDSON W. O. C. 2014 a. The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20 %. PLoS ONE 9 (3): e 91907. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0091907" title="The slugs of Britain and Ireland: undetected and undescribed species increase a well-studied, economically important fauna by more than 20" type="journal article" year="2014">ROWSON et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, all reddish specimens of 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C927FDF1A081FD99" box="[1110,1186,616,639]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. ater</emphasis>
s.l. from Britain that we have dissected are BR, which agrees with the results of 
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0CEE5FD3EA05CFD59" author="CHEVALLIER H." box="[916,1151,679,703]" journalOrPublisher="Universite de Paris" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref24757" refString="CHEVALLIER H. 1974. Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique. Ph. D. Thesis, Universite de Paris." title="Les grands Arion de France (Mollusca, Pulmonata). Taxonomie, biogeographie, ecologie, polymorphisme, croissance et cycle biologique" type="book" year="1974">
CHEVALLIER (
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0C947FD3EA055FD59" box="[1078,1142,679,703]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">1974</bibRefCitation>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Moreover, we have recently found the BR morphotype occurring commonly in Almondbury, now the type locality. In theory LISTER’ s (1685) red slugs might instead have been hybrids between BR and 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C911FCB1A0C1FCD9" box="[1120,1250,808,831]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. ater ater</emphasis>
, or improbably early occurrences of presumably non-native species such as 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0CEE3FCF1A02AFC99" box="[914,1033,871,895]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. vulgaris</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C944FCF1A08EFC99" box="[1077,1197,871,895]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. flagellus</emphasis>
. These possibilities could be made irrelevant to the issue of taxonomy with the designation of an appropriate neotype, as is our future intention. Our 
<taxonomicName id="3DBDD881A544FFA0C91CFC51A753FC19" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Arionidae" genus="Arion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="28" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subSpecies" species="ater" subSpecies="rufus">
<emphasis id="C8C97F10A544FFA0C91CFC51A13CFC39" box="[1133,1311,967,991]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Arion ater rufus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E2CDEF3A544FFA0C840FC5EA744FC19" author="LINNAEUS" journalOrPublisher="Salvius, Holmiae" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref26868" refString="LINNAEUS [LINNAEUS] C. 1758. Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata. Salvius, Holmiae. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" title="Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Editio decima, reformata" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
